PUTTING YOU AT ALMOST TWICE
AS MUCH AS ME.

11:53.920 --> 11:56.184
- NO, NOT AT TWICE AS MUCH.

11:56.300 --> 11:58.291
- THAT'S WHY I SAID "ALMOST."
DID YOU HEAR THAT PART?

11:58.400 --> 12:00.391
- CROSBY, WE AGREED
EACH TO TAKE 25% LESS

12:00.510 --> 12:01.954
THAN WE'D BEEN MAKING
TO MAKE THIS BUSINESS WORK.

12:02.060 --> 12:03.402
- YEAH, I REMEMBER.
- OKAY?

12:03.510 --> 12:05.023
THAT'S WHAT WE AGREED WAS FAIR.
- AND AT THAT TIME--

12:05.130 --> 12:07.507
AT THAT TIME, IT WAS FAIR.
BUT NOW I DON'T THINK IT'S FAIR.

12:07.620 --> 12:08.689
- CROSBY, I JUST TOLD YOU,

12:08.790 --> 12:09.370
I HAVE TO GET
OUT OF HERE EARLY, OKAY?

12:09.480 --> 12:10.924
I GOT A LOT ON MY PLATE,

12:11.040 --> 12:12.416
SO JUST ASK ME LATER.
LET ME FINISH THIS.

12:12.520 --> 12:13.748
- I'M NOT GONNA ASK YOU LATER.

12:13.870 --> 12:15.269
I DIDN'T WANT TO ASK YOU NOW.
THAT WAS NOT FUN.

12:15.380 --> 12:16.517
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE
TO DO THIS ALL OVER AGAIN.

12:16.630 --> 12:17.699
- ALL RIGHT,
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

12:17.800 --> 12:18.903
LET'S JUST WAIT
UNTIL THE END OF THE YEAR

12:19.010 --> 12:19.931
WHEN WE HAVE
A MORE COMPREHENSIVE VIEW--

12:20.040 --> 12:21.280
- THE END OF THE YEAR?
- YEAH.

12:21.390 --> 12:22.425
- THAT'S WHEN YOU W--OKAY.
- THE END OF THE YEAR.

12:22.530 --> 12:23.906
THAT'S WHEN I WANT
TO TALK ABOUT THAT, OKAY?

12:24.010 --> 12:25.147
- GREAT, GREAT.
MAYBE AT MY RETIREMENT PARTY,

12:25.260 --> 12:29.117
WE CAN DISCUSS
INCREASING MY S--

12:31.880 --> 12:34.121
- HEY, GUYS.

12:34.230 --> 12:37.290
HEY, DWAYNE.
- HEY, WHAT'S UP?

12:37.410 --> 12:40.470
- AW, JEEZ, I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR GIANTS LAST NIGHT.

12:40.580 --> 12:42.616
- IT'S ALL GOOD, ZEEK.
TOO BAD ABOUT YOUR A'S.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.893
- OH, REALLY?
TOUCHE, MAN. GOD.

12:45.000 --> 12:47.275
SIMON.
- HEY, MORNING, ZEEK.

12:47.380 --> 12:49.268
- MORNING.
HEY, I WANTED TO FOLLOW UP

12:49.380 --> 12:52.008
WITH YOU ABOUT A JOB PLACEMENT
FOR RYAN YORK.

12:52.110 --> 12:54.249
I--KID DID A BANG-UP JOB
ON MY SPRINKLERS,

12:54.350 --> 12:55.794
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?
- YEAH.

12:55.910 --> 12:56.899
- I MEAN, THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING FOR HIM.

12:57.010 --> 12:59.570
- YORK, YEAH, I GOT HIM
A JOB INTERVIEW.

12:59.670 --> 13:00.807
YEAH, BUT--BUT
HE WAS A NO-SHOW.

13:00.910 --> 13:03.492
- WHAT?
- HE BLEW IT OFF.

13:03.610 --> 13:05.532
- WELL, MAYBE HE GOT THE WRONG
INFORMATION OR SOMETHING.

13:05.640 --> 13:10.122
- MAYBE, BUT HE DIDN'T SHOW UP.
HASN'T SHOWN UP HERE FOR DAYS.

13:10.230 --> 13:12.266
DOESN'T EVEN
ANSWER HIS PHONE, MAN.

13:12.370 --> 13:15.237
KID'S AWOL.

13:15.340 --> 13:16.193
- HOW'S THAT HISTORY CLASS
THAT YOU WERE TELLING ME ABOUT?

13:16.310 --> 13:18.130
- OH, YEAH,
HE'S ACTUALLY FUNNY.

13:18.240 --> 13:20.162
HE'S ACTUALLY,
LIKE, REALLY FUNNY.

13:20.280 --> 13:22.271
I JUST DIDN'T GET
THAT HE WAS JOKING.

13:22.380 --> 13:24.792
HE'S LIKE, MAKES MEAN JOKES,
AND IT'S NOT, UH...

13:24.900 --> 13:26.413
NOT CLEAR AT FIRST.
- OKAY.

13:26.520 --> 13:29.148
- BUT ONCE YOU GET HIM...
- A LOT OF PEOPLE DON'T GET HIM.

13:29.250 --> 13:30.831
- GOOD, I LOVED HISTORY.
- YEAH, BUT NOW, I'M IN.

13:30.940 --> 13:32.828
- NOW YOU GET HIM.

13:32.950 --> 13:35.976
- MM-HMM.

13:36.090 --> 13:39.708
WHAT'S UP?
- NOTHING.

13:39.810 --> 13:41.675
- WE'RE JUST GLAD
THAT YOU'RE HAPPY.

13:41.780 --> 13:43.224
- YEAH...
- HADDIE, UM...

13:43.330 --> 13:47.232
SO IT TURNS OUT, UM,
I-I HAD TO GO--

13:47.340 --> 13:50.639
I WENT TO THE DOCTOR FOR MY--
FOR MY MAMMOGRAM,

13:50.760 --> 13:53.206
MY YEARLY MAMMOGRAM,
AND UM...

13:53.310 --> 13:56.029
THEY FOUND SOMETHING THERE.
- THEY FOUND A SMALL TUMOR.

13:56.140 --> 13:58.028
- JUST SMALL.
IT'S SO TINY.

13:58.140 --> 13:59.823
IT'S JUST MINISCULE.
THEY'RE GONNA, YOU KNOW,

13:59.940 --> 14:00.929
TAKE GOOD CARE OF IT.
I'M FINE.

14:01.040 --> 14:03.213
- TH EY--IT--YOU--
THEY FOUND CANCER.

14:03.320 --> 14:06.289
- IT IS--IT IS CANCER.
- YES.

14:06.390 --> 14:07.698
- BUT WE HAVE--
- YOUR MOM'S GOT GREAT DOCTORS,

14:07.810 --> 14:08.799
AND HER PROGNOSIS
LOOKS REALLY GOOD.

14:08.910 --> 14:10.320
- YEAH, WE FOUND
THE BEST DOCTORS.

14:10.430 --> 14:11.738
- WE DON'T WANT YOU TO WORRY.
WE JUST WANTED YOU TO KNOW.

14:11.850 --> 14:13.772
- YOU DON'T WANT ME TO WORRY,
BUT YOU HAVE BREAST CANCER?

14:13.880 --> 14:15.529
LIKE, IT'S EARLY.
- THIS HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

14:15.640 --> 14:16.709
VERY EARLY.
- LIKE, THEY CAUGHT IT EARLY?

14:16.820 --> 14:18.196
- YES.

14:18.300 --> 14:19.403
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME
TO SO MANY WOMEN, OKAY?

14:19.510 --> 14:21.603
YOU KNOW, THEY'RE GONNA GO IN
AND TAKE IT OUT,

14:21.720 --> 14:23.608
AND SO MANY WOMEN
SURVIVE FROM THIS,

14:23.720 --> 14:24.857
AND I'M GONNA BE
ONE OF THOSE WOMEN.

14:24.960 --> 14:26.928
- YEP.
- SO...

14:27.030 --> 14:28.270
- MM-HMM.
- OKAY?

14:28.380 --> 14:29.449
- YEAH.

14:29.550 --> 14:31.199
- PLEASE DON'T--
IT'S GONNA BE FINE, HONEY.

14:31.310 --> 14:32.891
I JUST--I DON'T
WANT YOU TO WORRY.

14:33.010 --> 14:34.511
WE JUST WANTED TO TELL YOU
BECAUSE--

14:34.630 --> 14:35.767
- YEAH, I JUST FEEL
LIKE I'M REALLY FAR AWAY.

14:35.870 --> 14:37.246
I DON'T KNOW--

14:37.350 --> 14:39.147
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M REALLY FAR AWAY FROM HOME.

14:39.250 --> 14:40.319
- ALL RIGHT.
- WE WANT--WE WANT YOU TO FOCUS

14:40.430 --> 14:42.045
ON SCHOOL, OKAY?
DON'T WORRY ABOUT YOUR MOM.

14:42.150 --> 14:44.425
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.
- AND WE WANT YOU TO HAVE FUN

14:44.530 --> 14:46.282
AND JUST...
- OKAY.

14:46.400 --> 14:47.662
WILL YOU CA--LIKE,
WHEN ARE YOU GOING IN?

14:47.780 --> 14:48.804
WILL YOU CALL ME?
WILL YOU, LIKE,

14:48.920 --> 14:50.228
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:50.330 --> 14:51.570
- WE'LL LET YOU KNOW...
- WE'LL KEEP YOU UP-TO-DATE.

14:51.680 --> 14:53.056
- EVERYTHING, OKAY?

14:53.160 --> 14:55.333
- DON'T WORRY.
YOU FOCUS ON YOURSELF, OKAY?

14:55.440 --> 14:57.408
- YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
- WE LOVE YOU VERY MUCH.

14:57.510 --> 15:00.684
- LOVE YOU. BYE-BYE.
- BYE, HONEY.

15:00.790 --> 15:02.929
[sighs]

15:22.020 --> 15:24.773
- UH, LAURA?
JULIA BRAVERMAN'S HERE.

15:24.880 --> 15:27.576
- NO WAY.
JULIA BRAVERMAN!

15:27.680 --> 15:30.956
- HI, LAURA.
WOW, THIS IS A BEAUTIFUL OFFICE.

15:31.060 --> 15:34.166
CONGRATULATIONS
ON ALL YOUR SUCCESS.

15:34.270 --> 15:34.998
- WELL, RUMOR HAS IT
YOU'RE NEXT IN LINE

15:35.100 --> 15:36.089
FOR PARTNER OVER AT DENGRAF.

15:36.210 --> 15:38.166
- WELL...
- THAT'S THE WORD ON THE STREET.

15:38.280 --> 15:40.419
- YEAH. THANK YOU.
- SO...

15:40.520 --> 15:41.487
- [clears throat]

15:41.590 --> 15:43.933
SO I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'VE HAD A CHANCE

15:44.040 --> 15:45.905
TO GO THROUGH
ALL THE PAPERWORK YET.

15:46.010 --> 15:48.387
- JULIA,
I KNOW THAT YOU FILED

15:48.490 --> 15:50.355
YOUR ANSWERS TO THE REQUEST
FOR ADMISSIONS LATE.

15:50.460 --> 15:53.975
- EXACTLY.
- MAJOR SCREW-UP.

15:54.090 --> 15:56.604
DID SOME FIRST-YEAR ASSOCIATE
SCREW IT UP?

15:56.710 --> 15:57.699
- NOPE, IT WAS ALL ME.

15:57.810 --> 16:01.985
- OH.

16:02.090 --> 16:04.058
- YES, AND I WAS WONDERING
IF THERE WAS ANY WAY

16:04.170 --> 16:05.717
THAT YOU COULD LOOK
THE OTHER WAY ON THIS.

16:05.820 --> 16:07.708
- JULIA...
[laughs]

16:07.820 --> 16:09.401
- LISTEN, ALL YOU'D HAVE
TO DO IS SAY

16:09.520 --> 16:11.545
THAT YOU AGREED
TO EXTEND THE DEADLINE.

16:13.210 --> 16:14.108
- YOU'RE ASKING ME
TO LOOK THE OTHER WAY

16:14.210 --> 16:16.314
AND POSSIBLY COST MY CLIENT

16:16.420 --> 16:19.173
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS
OF DOLLARS?

16:19.280 --> 16:23.421
- [chuckles] YES, THAT IS...
THAT IS WHAT I'M ASKING.

16:28.430 --> 16:31.183
OKAY.

16:31.300 --> 16:33.359
SO I ADOPTED
A NINE-YEAR-OLD BOY.

16:36.370 --> 16:39.191
AND IT HAS NOT
BEEN GOING SMOOTHLY,

16:39.300 --> 16:42.064
AND I HAVE NOT BEEN FOCUSED
AT WORK.

16:45.030 --> 16:50.935
I'M...BEGGING YOU.

16:51.040 --> 16:57.172
[dog barking]

16:58.980 --> 17:03.110
- ONE SEC.

17:03.220 --> 17:05.393
HEY--HEY.
- HEY.

17:05.500 --> 17:06.706
MAY I COME IN?

17:06.810 --> 17:09.256
- WHAT IS IT, THE SPRINKLERS
ARE DOWN AGAIN OR WHAT?

17:09.370 --> 17:12.407
- NO, NO, SPRINKLER SYSTEM'S
WORKING GREAT.

17:12.510 --> 17:15.434
MAN, THINGS ARE GOING OFF
RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

17:15.550 --> 17:17.609
UH, NO, YOU JUST HAVEN'T BEEN
TO THE VET CENTER

17:17.720 --> 17:19.779
FOR A FEW DAYS, RYAN.
- YOU MISS ME?

17:19.900 --> 17:22.277
- I GUESS, YEAH.

17:22.380 --> 17:24.439
- WELL, LISTEN,
AS MUCH AS I WOULD LOVE

17:24.560 --> 17:27.552
TO HEAR MORE STORIES
ABOUT FOXHOLES AND 'NAM,

17:27.660 --> 17:29.696
I'M TRYING TO LIVE MY LIFE.
- YEAH.

17:29.800 --> 17:32.314
WELL, YOU DIDN'T SHOW UP
FOR YOUR JOB INTERVIEW, RIGHT?

17:32.430 --> 17:35.661
- OH, SO THAT'S
WHY YOU'RE HERE.

17:35.770 --> 17:39.979
- I JUST KNOW THAT IT'S HARD
TO GET STARTED AGAIN.

17:40.090 --> 17:41.808
- NO, NO, I--

17:41.920 --> 17:43.194
OKAY, YOU WANT
TO KNOW THE REASON

17:43.300 --> 17:44.847
WHY I'M NOT GOING BACK
TO THE VET CENTER?

17:44.960 --> 17:45.949
BECAUSE I'M SICK OF PEOPLE

17:46.060 --> 17:47.982
LOOKING AT ME
LIKE I'M A VETERAN.

17:48.100 --> 17:49.192
LIKE THERE'S
SOMETHING WRONG WITH ME,

17:49.300 --> 17:50.471
LIKE IT'S BROKEN OR SOMETHING.
- I KNOW.

17:50.580 --> 17:52.263
- I DON'T WANT TO BE A VETERAN.
I'M JUST RYAN.

17:52.380 --> 17:55.065
AND THE REASON I DIDN'T GO
TO THE CRAPPY JOB INTERVIEW

17:55.170 --> 17:57.377
IS BECAUSE THE JOB SUCKED.

17:57.490 --> 17:58.616
- WELL, YOU'VE GOT
TO START SOMEWHERE, SON.

17:58.730 --> 18:00.379
- OKAY, SAVE IT
FOR SOMEONE WHO CARES.

18:00.490 --> 18:04.142
PLEASE,
DON'T COME BACK HERE, ZEEK.

18:04.250 --> 18:07.424
[cell phone rings]

18:10.390 --> 18:11.015
- HELLO.

18:11.120 --> 18:14.942
- HI, DAD.
- HEY.

18:15.050 --> 18:16.631
HOW YOU DOING?
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

18:16.750 --> 18:19.150
- MM-HMM.
- HADDIE...

18:19.270 --> 18:20.532
- YEAH, I CAN'T REALLY
STOP THINKING ABOUT MOM.

18:20.650 --> 18:22.675
- OKAY, WELL, THAT'S--
THAT'S NORMAL

18:22.790 --> 18:23.927
UNDER THESE CIRCUMSTANCES.

18:24.030 --> 18:26.885
WE JUST WANT YOU TO STAY
POSITIVE AND BE STRONG, OKAY?

18:27.000 --> 18:28.376
- YEAH, I-I'M, LIKE, KIND OF
HAVING A HARD TIME FOCUSING,

18:28.480 --> 18:30.960
LIKE I SHOULD
BE DOING SOMETHING.

18:31.070 --> 18:33.061
- LOOK, HADDIE, WE JUST--
WE JUST DON'T WANT YOU TO WORRY.

18:33.180 --> 18:34.488
YOU'VE GOT TO FOCUS
ON YOUR SCHOOLWORK, OKAY?

18:34.590 --> 18:35.511
WE'RE--WE'RE TAKING CARE
OF EVERYTHING.

18:35.630 --> 18:37.177
YOU JUST DON'T WORRY.
- YEAH.

18:37.280 --> 18:40.078
I DON'T HAVE ANY INFORMATION,
AND I'M REALLY FAR AWAY,

18:40.180 --> 18:41.283
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

18:41.390 --> 18:42.698
- YOU KNOW WHAT,
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

18:42.810 --> 18:44.118
DON'T WORRY, AND JUST FOCUS
ON YOUR BOOKS, OKAY?

18:44.220 --> 18:45.357
GIVE YOURSELF A LITTLE BIT OF--
- STOP, WHAT?

18:45.460 --> 18:47.189
- HUH?
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

18:47.290 --> 18:48.325
FOCUS ON SCHOOL?

18:48.430 --> 18:49.670
- JUST FOCUS ON SCHOOL.
DON'T BE--

18:49.780 --> 18:50.599
- DAD, IT'S, LIKE, HARD.

18:50.710 --> 18:52.985
I'M JUST REALLY FAR AWAY
FROM HOME.

18:53.090 --> 18:54.364
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON, LIKE,

18:54.470 --> 18:57.337
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
ANY INFORMATION.

18:57.440 --> 18:58.259
HELLO?

18:58.370 --> 19:02.682
CAN YOU TREAT ME
LIKE AN ADULT?

19:02.790 --> 19:07.306
- OKAY.

19:07.420 --> 19:12.346
YOUR MOTHER'S TUMOR
IS 1.6 CENTIMETERS, OKAY?

19:12.460 --> 19:15.588
SO THEY'RE GONNA BE ABLE
TO DO A LUMPECTOMY.

19:15.700 --> 19:16.974
THEY'RE GONNA BE ABLE
TO GET THE TUMOR OUT

19:17.080 --> 19:20.186
WITHOUT HAVING TO DO
A MASTECTOMY, SO THAT'S GOOD.

19:20.290 --> 19:21.700
AND--AND WHILE THEY'RE DOING
THE LUMPECTOMY,

19:21.810 --> 19:26.702
THEY'RE GONNA DO
A BIOPSY OF TWO LYMPH NODES

19:26.820 --> 19:28.435
BECAUSE THAT'S HOW CANCER
USUALLY SPREADS,

19:28.540 --> 19:29.711
SO THEY'RE GOING
TO BE ABLE TO TELL

19:29.820 --> 19:31.435
WHETHER YOUR MOTHER NEEDS
ANY FURTHER TREATMENT,

19:31.540 --> 19:35.920
CHEMOTHERAPY OR RADIATION,
ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

19:36.030 --> 19:37.895
OKAY?
- SO SHE MIGHT NEED CHEMO?

19:38.000 --> 19:41.299
- I'M NOT SAYING THAT.
SHE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

19:41.420 --> 19:43.103
BUT THAT'S THE TRUTH.
THAT'S AS MUCH AS I KNOW.

19:43.210 --> 19:46.099
THAT'S WHERE WE'RE AT.

19:46.210 --> 19:48.906
AND I PROMISE YOU
I WILL KEEP YOU UP-TO-DATE.

19:49.010 --> 19:51.934
I DON'T WANT YOU IN THE DARK.
- OKAY. HOW ARE YOU?

19:52.050 --> 19:55.463
- [laughs]

19:55.570 --> 19:59.085
YOU KNOW, I'M ALL RIGHT.
I'M HANGING IN THERE.

19:59.190 --> 20:00.873
YEP.

20:00.990 --> 20:05.677
IT'S SCARY,
BUT I'M OKAY.

20:05.790 --> 20:11.399
YEP.

20:11.520 --> 20:14.819
SO...YOU'VE GOT TO KNOW
THAT YOUR MOTHER IS...

20:14.930 --> 20:17.967
[sniffs] SO STRONG,
AND SHE'S SO POSITIVE,

20:18.070 --> 20:21.073
AND SHE IS DOING EVERYTHING
SHE CAN TO GET HEALTHY.

20:21.180 --> 20:24.525
AND THE BEST THING THAT YOU
CAN DO FOR YOUR MOM RIGHT NOW,

20:24.630 --> 20:27.838
HADDIE, IS JUST--
YOU JUST FOCUS ON SCHOOL.

20:27.950 --> 20:32.660
AND YOU DO WELL,
AND YOU MAKE HER PROUD, OKAY?

20:32.780 --> 20:35.749
CAN YOU DO THAT FOR ME?
- YEAH.

20:35.850 --> 20:39.741
- OKAY, GOOD.

20:39.850 --> 20:40.430
LISTEN, I'VE GOT TO GET
BACK TO WORK HERE,

20:40.540 --> 20:42.428
BUT I LOVE YOU, OKAY?

20:42.550 --> 20:45.064
- MM-HMM.
LOVE YOU TOO.

20:45.170 --> 20:49.129
- BYE.
[inhales deeply]

20:49.240 --> 20:52.960
[sighs]

21:02.330 --> 21:03.217
- AND YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT ALL THIS MEANS?

21:03.330 --> 21:04.467
- YEAH, MOM'S GOT CANCER.

21:04.570 --> 21:07.255
- OKAY.
- BUT I'M GONNA BE OKAY.

21:07.360 --> 21:08.748
- SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.
- OKAY.

21:08.850 --> 21:10.533
- BUT SHE'S GONNA HAVE
TO GO THROUGH SOME THINGS,

21:10.640 --> 21:11.572
NOT GONNA HAVE
AS MUCH TIME FOR YOU,

21:11.680 --> 21:12.988
SHE'S GONNA NEED TO REST,

21:13.090 --> 21:14.534
SHE'S GOING TO NEED TO GO
TO DOCTOR'S APPOINTMENTS.

21:14.650 --> 21:18.689
SO YOU'RE JUST GONNA HAVE
TO BE A LITTLE MORE GROWN UP.

21:18.790 --> 21:21.714
- OKAY.

21:25.420 --> 21:26.557
- DO YOU HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS, BUDDY?

21:26.660 --> 21:30.175
DO YOU WANT TO ASK ME
ANYTHING OR...?

21:30.280 --> 21:31.793
- CAN I WATCH TV NOW?

21:31.910 --> 21:33.525
I HAVE 30 MINUTES OF SCREEN TIME
BANKED FROM LAST NIGHT.

21:33.630 --> 21:37.498
- [chuckles]
SURE.

21:41.740 --> 21:42.843
- HMM.

21:42.950 --> 21:46.056
- THINK HE CARES?
THINK HE UNDERSTANDS?

21:46.160 --> 21:48.299
- YEAH.

21:54.720 --> 21:57.371
- WHY ARE ALL THESE PEOPLE
COMING TO MY GAME?

21:57.480 --> 21:59.129
- THEY'RE NOT "THESE PEOPLE,"
THEY'RE YOUR FAMILY.

21:59.240 --> 22:01.174
THEY'RE--THEY'RE OUR FAMILY.
THAT'S WHY THEY'RE COMING.

22:01.280 --> 22:03.589
- ONLY GRANDMA AND GRANDPA
CAME TO MY RECITAL. SO NOT FAIR.

22:03.700 --> 22:04.689
- QUIT WHINING. SUCH A BABY.
- I'M NOT WHINING!

22:04.800 --> 22:06.415
- THEY'RE COMING
TO THE GAME TOO.

22:06.530 --> 22:07.519
- YOU'RE THE ONE THAT'S WHINING.
- YOU'RE JUST A BABY.

22:07.630 --> 22:09.837
- HEY,
DON'T CALL HER THAT, OKAY?

22:09.940 --> 22:11.259
- I MIGHT NOT EVEN
GET IN THE GAME.

22:11.360 --> 22:12.327
- YOU'RE GONNA
GET INTO THE GAME.

22:12.430 --> 22:13.909
- I'M THE WORST PLAYER
ON THE TEAM.

22:14.020 --> 22:16.250
- OH, MY GOD.
- YOU GAVE ME TWO KNIVES.

22:16.360 --> 22:17.634
YOU NEED A KNIFE.
THERE.

22:17.750 --> 22:19.320
- MOM, DO I EVEN HAVE TO GO
TO THIS STUPID GAME?

22:19.440 --> 22:20.702
- [groans]
[alarm beeping]

22:20.820 --> 22:22.572
- THE FIRE ALARM WENT OFF!
- MOM.

22:22.680 --> 22:25.092
MOM, MOM,
THE FIRE ALARM WENT OFF.

22:25.200 --> 22:28.192
MOM!

22:28.310 --> 22:29.709
[faint]
THE EGGS ARE BURNING.

22:29.830 --> 22:31.161
[knife scraping loudly]
MOM!

22:31.280 --> 22:33.919
MOM, I AM TALKING TO YOU.
WHY ARE YOU NOT ANSWERING ME?

22:34.040 --> 22:37.032
- GUYS, WHAT IS GOING ON?
- MOM, THE EGGS ARE BURNING.

22:37.140 --> 22:38.209
- MOM, WE'RE NOT--DAD.

22:38.320 --> 22:40.242
- SYD, VICTOR,
GO TO THE OTHER ROOM.

22:40.350 --> 22:41.385
- WE DIDN'T EVEN GET OUR--
- NOW!

22:41.490 --> 22:42.422
- IT'S NOT FAIR!
- GO, GO!

22:42.530 --> 22:43.554
- DAD, IT'S NOT FAIR!

22:43.670 --> 22:47.777
[alarm beeping]
- HEY, HONEY.

22:47.880 --> 22:49.040
YOU OKAY?
- [hyperventilatlng]

22:49.160 --> 22:50.320
UH-UH, NO,
I'M NOT ALL RIGHT.

22:50.430 --> 22:53.365
- HEY, HEY, HEY, JULIA.

22:53.470 --> 22:55.916
HEY, HONEY, HONEY.
- [sobbing]

22:56.020 --> 22:57.647
- IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:57.750 --> 23:00.992
JUST BREATHE HERE, OKAY?
JUST BREATHE.

23:01.100 --> 23:03.443
- [exhales]
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

23:03.550 --> 23:04.642
ALL RIGHT, JUST BREATHE.
- [gaspmg]

23:04.760 --> 23:07.035
- JUST BREATHE.
- I CAN'T DO IT.

23:07.140 --> 23:08.232
IT'S TOO MUCH, I CAN'T--

23:08.350 --> 23:10.272
- WHAT CAN'T YOU DO? WHAT?
- I CAN'T...

23:10.380 --> 23:15.408
[shuddering]

23:15.530 --> 23:18.385
[soft rock music]

23:21.840 --> 23:23.728
- WELL, IT WAS GOOD
THAT YOU WENT TO SEE HIM.

23:23.850 --> 23:27.707
THAT WAS AMGMOOD THING.

23:27.820 --> 23:31.608
YEAH, I MEAN, HE ONLY SLAMMED
THE DOOR IN MY FACE.

23:31.720 --> 23:33.096
- WELL, AT LEAST HE KNEW
THAT THERE WAS SOMEONE

23:33.200 --> 23:36.408
WHO CARED ENOUGH ABOUT HIM
TO CHECK UP ON HIM.

23:36.510 --> 23:39.513
YOU KNOW, POOR KID,
HE'S PROBABLY CONFUSED.

23:39.620 --> 23:43.863
HE'S CERTAINLY ANGRY

23:43.970 --> 23:47.690
AND, UH, YOU KNOW,
DOESN'T KNOW WHERE HE BELONGS.

23:47.800 --> 23:48.141
- YEAH.

23:48.250 --> 23:52.971
- YEAH.

23:53.080 --> 23:57.016
IT WAS A LONG TIME
BEFORE YOU CAME BACK TO ME.

24:03.090 --> 24:06.981
- WELL, THANK GOD
I HAD SOMEONE TO COME BACK TO.

24:23.250 --> 24:26.595
- WHY ARE YOU STARING AT ME?

24:26.700 --> 24:29.214
- ARE YOU A GROWN-UP?
- WHY DO YOU ASK?

24:29.320 --> 24:34.496
- WELL, MY PARENTS SAID I NEED
TO BE MORE GROWN UP.

24:34.610 --> 24:38.671
SO ARE YOU A GROWN-UP?

24:38.780 --> 24:40.361
- WELL...
[sighs]

24:40.470 --> 24:44.304
I GUESS SO, YEAH.

24:44.410 --> 24:45.684
- YOU DON'T DRESS
LIKE A GROWN-UP.

24:45.790 --> 24:48.065
- NO, I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT,
I DON'T.

24:48.170 --> 24:52.174
- AND YOU'RE SHORTER
THAN A LOT OF GROWN-UPS.

24:52.280 --> 24:53.895
- THAT'S SO TRUE.

24:54.000 --> 24:56.412
- SO WHAT MAKES YOU
A GROWN-UP?

24:56.520 --> 24:59.626
- [sighs]

24:59.730 --> 25:03.006
WELL, UH, LET'S SEE,
I HAVE, UM...

25:03.120 --> 25:04.189
I HAVE A JOB.

25:04.290 --> 25:07.179
AND, UM,
I HAVE A CAR.

25:07.290 --> 25:09.042
AND I HAVE TO PAY BILLS

25:09.160 --> 25:13.529
AND JUST KIND OF DO STUFF
ON MY OWN, I GUESS.

25:13.650 --> 25:15.436
- YOU'RE NOT MARRIED.

25:15.540 --> 25:18.407
- NO, I'M NOT.

25:18.510 --> 25:19.716
- ALL OF THE ADULTS I KNOW
ARE MARRIED.

25:19.820 --> 25:22.402
SO WHEN ARE YOU
GETTING MARRIED?

25:22.520 --> 25:26.923
- WELL...I GUESS I'D HAVE
TO MEET THE RIGHT PERSON FIRST.

25:30.830 --> 25:31.933
- MY MOM'S GOT CANCER.

25:37.050 --> 25:39.450
- DO YOU WANT 1N?) TALK ABOUT IT?

25:39.570 --> 25:42.016
- OKAY.

25:45.780 --> 25:46.292
- HOW MANY ARE THERE?
GIVE ME TWO IF YOU CAN.

25:46.400 --> 25:50.052
- MM-HMM.

25:50.160 --> 25:52.094
- PRETTY GOOD
WITH THE STICKS, HMM.

25:52.200 --> 25:53.360
JUST GONNA START WITH THIS...
- OKAY.

25:53.480 --> 25:56.165
- AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

25:56.270 --> 25:56.577
[sighs]

25:56.690 --> 25:59.750
- [sighs]

25:59.860 --> 26:03.375
- IT'S THE LOW SODIUM,
YEAH.

26:03.490 --> 26:08.939
- HANK, I'M HAVING A TOUGH TIME
NOT TALKING ABOUT, YOU KNOW...

26:09.050 --> 26:10.278
- WHAT?
- LOOK, IT'S LIKE,

26:10.390 --> 26:12.699
THERE'S ONLY TWO PEOPLE
IN THIS OFFICE, YOU KNOW,

26:12.810 --> 26:14.289
SO I CAN'T JUST--
YOU CAN'T, LIKE, KISS ME...

26:14.400 --> 26:15.628
- OKAY--
- AND THEN I GO BACK

26:15.740 --> 26:16.877
TO PHOTOSHOP AND NEVER--
- IT WAS NOTHING, ALL RIGHT?

26:16.980 --> 26:18.845
IT WAS NOTHING.
- NO, I DO UNDERSTAND--

26:18.950 --> 26:20.429
- ALL RIGHT, IT WAS NOTHING.
YOU GOT CLOSE TO ME.

26:20.540 --> 26:22.747
- I GOT CLOSE TO YOU?
I GOT--

26:22.850 --> 26:25.717
OH, I GOT--I GET IT.
NO, I GOT TOO CLOSE.

26:25.820 --> 26:26.809
I'M SORRY.
THAT WAS, YOU KNOW--

26:26.930 --> 26:28.886
- YOU DIDN'T GET TOO CLOSE.
I JUST...

26:29.000 --> 26:32.333
- OH, CLOSE ENOUGH
THAT YOUR REFLEX IS JUST TO...

26:32.450 --> 26:33.929
KISS ME?
THAT'S--I DIDN'T--

26:34.040 --> 26:35.996
I DIDN'T KNOW
THERE WAS A BOUNDARY THERE.

26:36.110 --> 26:39.728
- IT WAS NOTHING, IT WAS...
- OH, MY GOD.

26:39.830 --> 26:41.593
- [laughs]
YOU CAN'T HELP YOURSELF?

26:41.700 --> 26:43.008
I MEAN, I KNOW,
I'M DELIGHTFUL.

26:43.110 --> 26:44.759
- ALL RIGHT, COME ON,
JUST CUT IT OUT.

26:44.870 --> 26:45.313
YOU'RE NOT ALL THAT,
OKAY, SO...

26:45.430 --> 26:47.421
- WHAT?

26:47.530 --> 26:48.383
- ALL RIGHT,
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.

26:48.500 --> 26:50.218
- I-I--
- JUST, I'M SORRY.

26:50.330 --> 26:51.774
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.
- I'M NOT ALL THAT, YET...

26:51.880 --> 26:54.053
I MEAN, I UNDERSTAND.
- I DIDN'T MEAN IT, ALL RIGHT?

26:54.160 --> 26:56.082
- OKAY, NO, IT'S FINE.
- I JUST WANNA HAVE LUNCH.

26:56.200 --> 26:57.952
- I'M NOT ALL THAT.
THAT'S GOOD, 'CAUSE NOW I KNOW

26:58.060 --> 26:59.197
YOU HAVE NO--YOU DON'T--
- CAN'T I JUST EAT IN PEACE?

26:59.300 --> 27:01.052
- CAN IJUST EAT IN PEACE?
- COME ON.

27:01.170 --> 27:03.195
- CAN I JUST WORK
IN THE DARKROOM IN PEACE?

27:03.310 --> 27:04.379
IT'S LIKE, NOW I DON'T KNOW
IF SOMETHING'S GONNA HAPPEN,

27:04.480 --> 27:05.447
LIKE IF I GET
TOO IN YOUR SPACE--

27:05.550 --> 27:09.680
- FINE, OKAY,
IT WASN'T NOTHING.

27:09.800 --> 27:10.824
- WELL, I DON'T--
I DIDN'T MEAN--

27:10.930 --> 27:14.650
YOU KNOW, I'M NOT--
[sighs]

27:14.770 --> 27:20.003
- IT WASN'T NOTHING.

27:20.120 --> 27:22.634
YOU'RE FUNNY.

27:22.740 --> 27:25.664
YOU'RE PRETTY,
YOU'RE NICE...

27:25.780 --> 27:29.876
I LIKE TALKING TO YOU.

27:32.990 --> 27:35.094
AND H KNOW
YOU GOT SOMEBODY.

27:35.200 --> 27:39.159
SO LET'S JUST LEAVE IT
AT THAT, ALL RIGHT?

27:39.270 --> 27:41.135
OKAY? PLEASE?

27:41.240 --> 27:43.686
- YEAH.

27:51.840 --> 27:55.697
[knock at door]

27:55.810 --> 27:56.799
- YOU WANNA KNOW SOMETHING?

27:56.910 --> 27:58.730
YOU WERE RUDE TO ME BEFORE.

27:58.840 --> 27:59.943
- LOOK, OLD MAN--
- NO, NO, NO, NO.

28:00.050 --> 28:00.869
YOU'RE DOING IT AGAIN.
YOU DON'T DO THAT.

28:00.980 --> 28:03.289
YOU SHOW A LITTLE RESPECT.

28:03.400 --> 28:05.539
- HEY, WHATEVER YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING HERE,

28:05.640 --> 28:07.437
WHATEVER YOU THINK
IS GOING ON HERE,

28:07.540 --> 28:10.100
YOU'VE GOT TO STOP, ALL RIGHT?
I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

28:10.200 --> 28:12.919
- OKAY, I WILL TELL YOU
WHAT I THINK IS GOING ON HERE.

28:13.030 --> 28:14.304
I THINK YOU'RE SITTING AROUND
IN YOUR CRAPPY LITTLE APARTMENT

28:14.410 --> 28:16.992
HAVING YOUR OWN LITTLE PITY
PARTY GOING ON IN YOUR HEAD,

28:17.100 --> 28:20.103
AND YOU'RE NOT SPENDING
ENOUGH TIME

28:20.210 --> 28:21.689
THINKING ABOUT YOUR FUTURE,
RYAN YORK.

28:21.800 --> 28:23.347
- DID YOU JUST COME HERE
TO ANALYZE ME?

28:23.460 --> 28:25.348
IS THAT WHY YOU'RE HERE?

28:25.460 --> 28:29.180
- NO. I CAME HERE TO INVITE YOU
TO A BASEBALL GAME.

28:29.290 --> 28:31.042
YOU A BASEBALL FAN?

28:31.150 --> 28:33.391
- YEAH.
YEAH, THE GIANTS IN TOWN?

28:33.500 --> 28:36.355
- YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

28:36.470 --> 28:40.327
[indistinct chatter]

28:40.440 --> 28:41.919
YEAH, COME HERE.

28:42.030 --> 28:43.577
NOW THERE'S SOME PEOPLE HERE
I WANT YOU TO MEET, ALL RIGHT?

28:43.680 --> 28:45.090
- THIS ISN'T EXACTLY WHAT I...
- HEY, UH, EVERYBODY,

28:45.200 --> 28:47.475
I WANT YOU TO MEET
A REAL HERO HERE.

28:47.580 --> 28:48.683
- HI.
YOU MUST BE RYAN.

28:48.790 --> 28:49.950
- HI.
- HI, I'M CAMILLE.

28:50.070 --> 28:51.549
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- THIS IS RYAN YORK.

28:51.660 --> 28:52.854
- I'M SO GLAD YOU COULD MAKE IT.
- THIS IS MY SON ADAM.

28:52.970 --> 28:53.891
- HI.
- HOW YOU DOING, RYAN?

28:54.000 --> 28:56.412
ADAM.
- HOW ARE YOU?

28:56.520 --> 28:57.623
- CROSBY.
- THAT'S MAX.

28:57.730 --> 28:59.004
AND THERE'S
MY LOVELY DAUGHTER SARAH

28:59.110 --> 29:02.238
AND HER FRIEND, MARK.
HI, MARK.

29:02.360 --> 29:03.907
AND THAT'S DREW THERE.

29:04.010 --> 29:05.216
- EXCUSE ME.
- AND THAT'S CAMILLE AND JABBAR

29:05.320 --> 29:07.015
AND SYDNEY AND JULIA AND JOEL,
AND THERE'S JASMINE

29:07.120 --> 29:09.281
AND CROSBY.
- THERE'S A LOT OF US.

29:09.400 --> 29:10.879
- THESE ARE MY KIDS.
DID I MISS ANYBODY?

29:10.990 --> 29:12.150
OH, AMBER. AMBER.

29:12.260 --> 29:14.080
HOW COULD I FORGET AMBER?
- HI. RYAN.

29:14.200 --> 29:15.292
- I KEEP THE FAMILY TOGETHER.
HOW'S IT GOING?

29:15.400 --> 29:16.958
- LAST BUT NOT LEAST.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

29:17.060 --> 29:19.199
- YOU HAVE A SEAT.
AND VICTOR'S OUT THERE,

29:19.300 --> 29:21.029
SO, UH, COME ON, SIT DOWN,
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME,

29:21.130 --> 29:23.849
AND HAVE A GOOD TIME.
ALL RIGHT.

29:23.960 --> 29:27.657
- [sharp exhale]
YEAH.

29:27.760 --> 29:30.581
HI.
- HI.

29:30.690 --> 29:33.523
[cheers and applause]

29:33.630 --> 29:35.484
[soft rock music]

29:38.700 --> 29:39.974
- SEE,
I DON'T KNOW

29:40.080 --> 29:40.830
WHY THE HELL THEY'RE NOT
PUTTING VICTOR IN THE GAME.

29:40.950 --> 29:42.520
- I DON'T KNOW EITHER.

29:42.640 --> 29:44.221
- YOU KNOW, I'M THINKING ABOUT
GOING TO TALK TO THE COACH.

29:44.330 --> 29:48.460
- ZEEK, DO NOT
UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES

29:48.570 --> 29:49.889
TALK TO THE COACH.
- HOW COME?

29:49.990 --> 29:51.810
[cell phone rings]
- HI.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.091
- DID YOU GET MY TEXTS?
- NO, WHAT?

29:53.200 --> 29:56.499
- DENGRAF IS HERE.
THEY'RE ALL HERE.

29:56.620 --> 29:57.848
HE SAID THEY NEED
TO SEE YOU NOW.

29:57.960 --> 29:59.996
- 20 MINUTES.

30:00.100 --> 30:01.442
I HAVE TO GO TO WORK.
- NOW?

30:01.550 --> 30:02.869
- YEAH.
- EVERYTHING OKAY?

30:02.970 --> 30:04.619
- NO, I DON'T THINK IT IS.

30:04.730 --> 30:08.837
- I LOVE YOU.
- LOVE YOU.

30:08.940 --> 30:10.669
- WHERE THE HELL IS SHE GOING?
- ZEEK, PLEASE.

30:10.770 --> 30:14.809
- JEEZ.

30:14.910 --> 30:18.255
- THERE WE GO.
CAN I HAVE ONE?

30:18.360 --> 30:21.773
OH, I'LL TAKE THE FISH.
I LIKE THE FISH.

30:21.880 --> 30:23.677
- [whines]
- YOU WANNA GET ONE?

30:23.780 --> 30:26.408
YEAH, YOU GET ONE FOR YOURSELF.
HI.

30:26.510 --> 30:27.954
- CAN WE TALK
ABOUT THAT CONVERSATION

30:28.060 --> 30:29.197
WE HAD THE OTHER DAY?
- LISTEN, CROS...

30:29.310 --> 30:30.334
- YEAH, I KNOW
YOU DON'T HAVE TIME FOR IT.

30:30.440 --> 30:31.953
- HOLD ON.
- BUT I NEED TO HAVE THIS, OKAY?

30:32.070 --> 30:33.139
LISTEN, IT'S NOT
EVEN ABOUT THE MONEY.

30:33.240 --> 30:35.447
IT REALLY ISN'T.
IT'S ABOUT HOW YOU TREAT ME.

30:35.550 --> 30:37.177
- ALL RIGHT, CROS, CAN I JUST--
- I'M SICK OF IT, OKAY?

30:37.280 --> 30:39.271
YOU HAVE THIS CRAZY FAMILY
DYNAMIC YOU'RE HOLDING ONTO

30:39.380 --> 30:40.381
WHERE YOU'RE
THE GENIUS OLDER BROTHER

30:40.490 --> 30:41.969
AND I'M
THE IDIOT YOUNGER BROTHER,

30:42.080 --> 30:43.650
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,
THAT MAY WORK AT MOM AND DAD'S

30:43.770 --> 30:44.976
AT A HOLIDAY OR SOMETHING,
BUT AT WORK?

30:45.080 --> 30:47.878
WHEN I WANT TO TALK,
WE'RE GONNA TALK, ALL RIGHT?

30:47.980 --> 30:49.595
I'M DOING MORE THAN HALF
THE WORK RIGHT NOW.

30:49.700 --> 30:51.941
YOU'VE GOT AMBER RUNNING AROUND
DOING ALL OF THIS CRAP

30:52.050 --> 30:53.119
THAT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH THE LUNCHEONETTE.

30:53.230 --> 30:55.915
YOU ARE ACTING
LIKE A JACKASS.

31:03.030 --> 31:05.260
- OKAY.
- OKAY?

31:05.380 --> 31:09.089
- YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M WRONG.

31:09.210 --> 31:10.234
MONDAY MORNING,
WE'LL FIX YOUR SALARY.

31:10.350 --> 31:14.411
AND I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.
I'M SORRY.

31:16.940 --> 31:19.932
[exhales heavily]

31:23.980 --> 31:26.426
SWEETIE...

31:26.530 --> 31:28.179
- [babbling]
- WHAT?

31:28.300 --> 31:30.018
- MAMA, MAMA.
- THEY'RE REALLY CLOSE BY.

31:30.120 --> 31:31.087
DO YOU WANT
TO GIVE ME ONE MORE?

31:31.190 --> 31:36.298
[cheers and applause]

31:39.440 --> 31:43.968
- ARE YOU GONNA HAVE
TO GET CHEMOTHERAPY?

31:44.070 --> 31:45.799
- I DON'T KNOW, BUDDY.

31:45.900 --> 31:48.061
I MIGHT.
I'M NOT SURE.

31:48.180 --> 31:52.002
- YOU KNOW THAT IT KILLS
THE HEALTHY CELLS TOO, RIGHT?

31:52.110 --> 31:53.418
- I'M GONNA BE OKAY,
BUD.

31:53.530 --> 31:54.280
- I KNOW.
- OKAY.

31:54.390 --> 31:57.518
[scattered cheers and applause]

31:57.630 --> 32:01.327
- UH, EXCUSE ME, COACH,
CAN YOU PUT VICTOR IN THE GAME?

32:01.430 --> 32:04.081
- YEAH, WHAT ABOUT VICTOR?
- GUYS...

32:04.190 --> 32:06.533
- I MEAN, EVERY OTHER KID
IS PLAYING OUT THERE.

32:06.640 --> 32:08.392
- NO, HE'S RIGHT, HE--SOMEONE
SHOULD GO TALK TO THAT GUY.

32:08.510 --> 32:11.229
- COME ON, COACH.
- OH, MY GOD, YOU FIT RIGHT IN.

32:11.340 --> 32:12.921
- HERE WE GO.
- OH, THIS SHOULD BE GOOD.

32:13.030 --> 32:14.065
- HEY, HEY, COME ON, ZEEK.

32:14.170 --> 32:15.956
- YEAH, HEY, COACH,
HOW YOU DOING?

32:16.070 --> 32:17.162
- ZEEK.
- SIR, WHAT--

32:17.280 --> 32:18.406
- ZEEK BRAVERMAN HERE, HI.

32:18.520 --> 32:19.919
- YOU CAN'T BE ON THE FIELD
DURING THE GAME.

32:20.040 --> 32:22.508
- I KNOW THE RULES OF BASEBALL.
I MEAN, COME ON.

32:22.630 --> 32:25.758
I ALSO KNOW THAT MY GRANDSON HAS
BEEN BENCHED THE ENTIRE GAME.

32:25.870 --> 32:26.962
THERE'S ONLY ONE OUT LEI-T,

32:27.080 --> 32:29.696
SO I THOUGHT MAYBE
WE COULD HAVE A CHITCHAT.

32:29.800 --> 32:31.495
- IT'S TOO CLOSE TO PUT HIM IN.
THIS GAME'S TOO CLOSE.

32:31.600 --> 32:34.569
THERE'LL BE OTHER GAMES, ZEEK.
IT'S A LONG SEASON.

32:34.670 --> 32:36.149
- WELL, IF YOU DON'T PUT HIM
IN THE GAME NOW,

32:36.260 --> 32:37.295
HE MAY NOT SHOW UP
FOR THE OTHER GAMES, ALL RIGHT?

32:37.400 --> 32:39.948
I MEAN,
I GOT 15 MEMBERS

32:40.060 --> 32:41.982
OF THE BRAVERMAN FAMILY
SITTING RIGHT THERE,

32:42.090 --> 32:43.432
AND MOST OF THEM HAVE PLAYED
ON THIS FIELD

32:43.540 --> 32:45.747
AT ONE TIME OR ANOTHER.
HEY, ADAM, RAISE YOUR HAND.

32:45.860 --> 32:46.952
RAISE YOUR HAND, SON.

32:47.060 --> 32:48.402
HE WAS THE MOST VALUABLE PLAYER
IN 1978.

32:48.510 --> 32:51.263
HE WAS ONE OF THE BEST
SHORTSTOPS YOU EVER SAW.

32:51.380 --> 32:54.349
HAD GREAT HANDS, ALL RIGHT?
AND THAT KID RIGHT THERE,

32:54.450 --> 32:56.304
HIS NAME'S RYAN YORK.
HE'S JUST BACK FROM AFGHANISTAN.

32:56.420 --> 32:58.445
HE RISKED HIS LIFE
TO MAKE SURE

32:58.560 --> 33:01.028
THAT WE COULD PLAY BASEBALL
ON AMERICAN SOIL.

33:01.150 --> 33:03.141
- WE GOT A PROBLEM HERE?

33:03.250 --> 33:04.558
- NO, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT THE PROBLEM--

33:04.670 --> 33:07.070
THE PROB--LOOK, IS IT REALLY
ABOUT WINNING THE GAME,

33:07.190 --> 33:08.077
OR IS IT ABOUT
JUST PUTTING THE KIDS IN

33:08.190 --> 33:10.533
AND LETTING THEM PARTICIPATE

33:10.640 --> 33:12.153
AND, YOU KNOW,
FEELING LIKE THEY BELONG

33:12.260 --> 33:13.488
AND JUST HAVING
A DAMN GOOD TIME!

33:13.610 --> 33:18.081
- WOULD YOU JUST PUT THE KID
IN THE GAME?

33:18.200 --> 33:21.476
- UH, YEAH,
YOU WANNA DEAL WITH THAT?

33:21.580 --> 33:24.231
- VICTOR, GET YOUR HELMET ON.
- ALL RIGHT!

33:24.340 --> 33:25.238
[Bravermans cheering
and applauding]

33:25.340 --> 33:26.272
- ALL RIGHT!
- VICTOR!

33:26.380 --> 33:27.301
- PLEASE,
BACK IN THE STANDS, SIR.

33:27.410 --> 33:31.107
- I'M GOING.
- VICTOR!

33:31.210 --> 33:32.177
- GO, VICTOR!
- HEY, VICTOR!

33:32.280 --> 33:34.032
RELAX LIKE WE TALKED ABOUT.

33:34.150 --> 33:36.721
YOU GOT THIS, BUDDY.

33:36.840 --> 33:37.693
- EASY, BUDDY.

33:37.800 --> 33:38.482
- SOCK IT, KIDDO!

33:38.600 --> 33:40.659
- YOU GOT THIS, MAN.

33:40.770 --> 33:43.284
- VICTOR!

33:43.400 --> 33:46.255
[overlapping shouting]
- OH, MAN.

33:46.360 --> 33:47.770
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S OKAY, THAT'S OKAY.

33:47.880 --> 33:50.917
- COME ON, VICTOR.
- SOCK IT, KIDDO!

33:51.020 --> 33:52.840
- NICE, EASY SWING, VIC.

33:52.960 --> 33:54.188
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

33:54.300 --> 33:56.609
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SWING
AT EVERY ONE, BUDDY.

33:56.720 --> 33:58.506
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO KILL IT,
JUST MEET THE BALL.

33:58.620 --> 34:00.611
OKAY, SNAP THOSE WRISTS.
- JUST MAKE CONTACT.

34:00.720 --> 34:03.063
[Edward Sharpe and
the Magnetic Zeros' Man on Fire]

34:03.170 --> 34:09.450
- [humming]

34:14.630 --> 34:19.283
OH, MM
[cheers and applause]

34:19.400 --> 34:22.221
COME DANCE WITH ME

34:22.330 --> 34:27.916
OVER MURDER AND PAIN

34:28.030 --> 34:31.056
- YEAH, YES, GO!
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

34:31.170 --> 34:32.785
